text:
The deadline to compete for the Congressional App Challenge  
is quickly approaching. If you are a middle or high school student interested in competing in the Congressional App Challenge, I encourage you to apply at the link below by November 1!
 guthrie.house.gov/services/c…

Last week, I met with the KY Federation of State, County, and Municipal Employees to discuss concerns of those who serve our communities. I’m a proud cosponsor of H.R. 82 which would eliminate the WEP and GPO to ensure those that paid into Social Security receive these benefits.

As we enter Breast Cancer Awareness month in October, Beth & I pray for those battling this terrible disease. As Chair of @HouseCommerce Health Subcommittee, I will continue fighting for solutions that drive innovation for patients that ultimately cure cancer once and for all.
I had a great time taking my friend Warren County Sheriff Brett Hightower and his family around the Capitol Building last week.
I’m proud to stand with my friend @SpeakerMcCarthy.

I appreciate Major General Edward Merrigan, Commander of the 84th Training Command of the United States Army Reserve at Fort Knox, meeting with me to discuss the issues important to our men and women at Fort Knox.

With most of the nation within a day’s drive of Kentucky, our truck drivers are at the heart of keeping our economy running. This week I met with the KY Truckload Carriers Association & KY Truck Trailers Manufacturers Association to discuss the challenges within their industry.
Today I questioned our nation’s grid operators on the status of our electric grid and why Washington liberals’ rush to green agenda would be harmful to Kentuckians. Check it out!

DEADLINE APPROACHING: Are you a veteran who left military service between 9/11/01-10/1/13 and are eligible for benefits from the PACT Act? You have until 11:59PM on 9/30 to apply at the link below. For more info, call my office at (270)-842-9896. va.gov/resources/the-pact-ac…
I recently met with partners from the White Oak Initiative to discuss best practices on white oak sustainability to ensure we can continue to have this vital Kentucky resource.

Last night, I voted Yea on the Protecting Hunting Heritage and Education Act, which I’m proud to co-sponsor. Archery and hunting provide valuable lessons to our youth and I am proud to help protect these programs from President Biden’s recent attack on our 2nd Amendment rights.
Last week, I enjoyed meeting with Kentucky Head Start leaders to discuss education policy and the critical work they do to help ensure our children succeed in school and in life.

I was happy to welcome the @GOchamber to the U.S. Capitol with @LeaderMcConnell! We discussed growing our local economy & community. I also enjoyed giving a brief tour to talk about the history of our nation & my favorite painting- the Signing of the Declaration of Independence.

I enjoyed meeting with Kentuckians from the @AAOS1  to talk about issues impacting the healthcare community including the workforce challenges. We need to have qualified individuals to take care of us when we need them most!
I enjoyed meeting with @GoCards Athletic Director @joshheird to discuss the future of college athletics.

This week I enjoyed meeting with Kentuckians with the @AmericanCancer Society Cancer Action Network. We discussed the great need to conquer cancer in our lifetime, by increasing access to diagnostics and cures that can help Americans live longer healthier lives.

As Health Subcommittee Chair of @housecommerce, I’m working to help patients get access to life changing treatments. Yesterday, I spoke at @ASGCTherapy’s Policy Summit to provide an update on the MVP Act which I introduced in the House to provide access to gene therapies.

Yesterday, former Governor Brereton Jones passed away. Beth and I send our thoughts and prayers to his friends and family.
wlky.com/article/former-kent…
Happy 76th Birthday to the @usairforce! Thank you to all the airmen who protect and defend our skies and our nation! And thank you to all Air Force veterans for your service to our nation!

On Constitution Day we honor the foundational document that defends the rights of “We the People”. I’ve taken the oath many times in my life. First was as a cadet at West Point and this past January as your Congressman for the 118 Congress. I work every day to uphold this oath.

This week I received the AbilityOne Program’s Champion Award. I’m committed to helping empower Kentuckians with disabilities to showcase their skills in our workforce. Their largest program is right here in Hardin County!

I enjoyed visiting the @GOchamber for their September Rooster Booster breakfast! It was great to honor Owensboro’s 40 under 40 that help make the community thrive and I look forward to seeing what these leaders do next.

Today, we honor and recognize the brave Americans who were Prisoners of War and those who never came back home. I display the POW/MIA Flag in my D.C. office, alongside the U.S. and Kentucky flag as a reminder of the great sacrifice these soldiers made.
If you're interested in applying, please contact my Bowling Green office at 270-842-9896 for more information!

As a @WestPoint_USMA grad, I'm proud to see so many of our students interested in applying to a service academy. Thank you to everyone who spoke with students and their families about their experiences.

thenewsenterprise.com/news/l…

Catch the rest of our 15-minute interview here!
piped.video/pzitt_h2C-c
Didn’t get a chance to listen earlier? Here is a clip of my interview with @SpeakerMcCarthy this afternoon!
I was so sorry to hear of the loss of my colleague @Rep_Peltola’s husband Eugene “Buzzy” Peltola Jr. My thoughts and prayers are with you and your family.

Check out my interview with @SpeakerMcCarthy on WHAS 840 the @terrymeiners show at 4:30 PM ET.

iheart.com/live/news-radio-8…

I’m honored to support our Kentucky National Guard. From aiding our communities during natural disaster, to conducting counter drug programming in Kentucky, and deploying overseas- our National Guard always answers the call. Thank you for taking time to meet with me yesterday.

I recently toured the Green County Area Technology Center where I met with students learning to weld and met recent graduates at their new jobs. College isn’t for everyone, and I’m proud to support programs that allow students to pursue other lucrative and fulfilling careers.
It was my pleasure to join the Barren County 225th anniversary celebration in Glasgow. I look forward to the next 225 years of Barren’s future successes!

Today, we honor those who lost their lives in the horrific attacks on September 11, 2001. May God bless those who lost their lives, their families, those impacted by these callous acts, and may God bless our first responders who sacrifice their lives every day to keep us safe.

I brought together officials with over 228 years of law enforcement experience to hear firsthand how we can solve the overdose crisis in KY. We had an engaging conversation on how to keep these poisons off our streets and get those with substance use disorder the help they need!

I enjoyed spending time with Louisville Metro Councilman Tony Piagentini to discuss how we can best serve our constituents in Eastern Jefferson County, including how we can work together to boost economic growth in the area.

REMINDER: Monday, September 11 is my 2023 Service Academy Information Fair for students and their families in Kentucky’s 2nd District. Representatives from the U.S. Service Academies will be present to answer your questions about the application process.

President Biden is defying common sense to block American energy production in Alaska. Kentuckians are hurting at the pump. We must stop relying on adversaries like Venezuela for our energy and make America energy independent again. foxnews.com/politics/biden-a…

Beth and I send our thoughts and prayers to the Louisville police officer in critical condition after being shot this morning.

wdrb.com/news/crime-reports/…

This September we celebrate National Recovery Month. As Health Subcommittee Chair, curbing substance use disorder will remain a top priority of mine. That’s why my SUPPORT Act provides comprehensive recovery support services to those seeking overcome substance use disorder.

Are you a veteran eligible for benefits from the PACT Act who served between September 11, 2001 and October 1, 2013? You have until 11:59PM on September 30th to apply for benefits at this link. For more information, please call my Bowling Green office. va.gov/resources/the-pact-ac…
Happy Labor Day! Thank you to everyone who keeps our country running!
I recently sat down with the @bgdailynews to discuss my legislative accomplishments and goals and how they will impact Kentuckians. Check it out:

On International Overdose Awareness Day, I'm praying for those who have lost loved ones to substance use disorder. As Health Subcommittee Chair I’m committed to supporting policies that help those seeking to overcome substance use disorder and prevent it from occurring entirely.
I enjoyed talking with my friends with the Meade County Farm Bureau about the work House Republicans are doing to support our family farmers, including lower energy costs.

I’m issuing the challenge to our talented middle and high school students to compete for the most prestigious prize in computer science. I look forward to seeing this year’s students’ apps. The deadline to submit is November 1. For more information, check out the video below.
Beth and I are praying for our friend and colleague @SteveScalise. No one fights harder than our Majority Leader. We wish you a full and speedy recovery.

I’m looking forward to hosting the 2023 Service Academy Information Fair on September 11 for students and their families in Kentucky's 2nd District. U.S. Service Academy representatives will be present to answer questions about the application process. Please RSVP to my office.

Wishing everyone across the 2nd District a great school year! If you or your school is ever in Washington D.C., make sure to give my office a call (at 202-225-3501) to request a tour of the U.S. Capitol and White House!

I visited the Barren River Child Advocacy Center to discuss the work they do to support children who have experienced abuse. Child Advocacy Centers in Kentucky not only provide wraparound services to assist with healing but also help law enforcement provide justice to children.

I enjoyed seeing the newly restored Mammoth Cave Stagecoach. This unique piece of history is a great reminder of the remarkable achievements of past Kentuckians and of the fantastic history in the 2nd district!

I enjoyed my recent meeting with Hart County Tourism Director Sandra Wilson and local business owners. We discussed how we can bring even more visitors to see the beauty that Hart County has to offer!
Beth and I send our deepest condolences and prayers to you, Sara Jane and the entire Van Orden family during this incredibly difficult time.

I enjoyed gathering with folks in Auburn this week.  I share their concerns about rising costs that are affecting our everyday lives. I’m committed to fighting inflation and the runaway spending from the Biden Administration policies.

I was happy to speak with some longtime friends at the Breckinridge County Chamber of Commerce Lunch this week to discuss the work I’m doing in Congress to make sure we have reliable and affordable energy.

I held a roundtable with community leaders to discuss how we can combat the drug overdose crisis and help people seeking to overcome substance use disorder. I am proud to be leading the SUPPORT Act to prevent future overdoses and promote long-term recovery.pmg-ky2.com/kystandard/news/…

I visited the Fairview Community Health Clinic in Bowling Green to discuss the work I am doing in Congress to reauthorize health care programs that will help the dedicated clinical team at Fairview Community Health Clinic continue to provide these essential health services.

I joined my colleagues from @HouseCommerce to demand answers on @SecGranholm’s meetings with Chinese officials just days before the Biden admin raided our Strategic Petroleum Reserves in 2021. What was discussed in these meetings with the CCP?foxnews.com/politics/energy-…

I spoke with the Green River Area Development District, who serve numerous counties in KY-02, about the work I’m doing as Chair of the Health Subcommittee and how health care price transparency can help lower health care costs for Kentuckians and their families.

I enjoyed visiting with folks at Ohio County Farm Bureau’s annual meeting on how we can find new markets for Kentucky agricultural products to help decrease our trade deficits and how we can address labor shortages.

Central City has a strong economic and cultural heritage and was the home of many great musicians including the Everly Brothers. I was honored to participate in Central City’s 150th Anniversary Celebration to honor the rich history and culture of this iconic city!

As Co-Chair of the Job Corps Caucus, I’m a strong supporter of the work they do to equip our young people with the skills they need to be successful in the workforce. Today, I toured the Muhlenberg County Job Corps to see the important work they’re doing!

Are you a veteran or survivor eligible for benefits from the PACT ACT? You have until 11:59pm Monday August 14th to apply at the link below! For additional information, please contact my district office at (270) 842-9896.
va.gov/disability/file-disab…

I had an informative visit yesterday at @BRElectricCorp  in Owensboro talking with energy sector leaders about the Biden administration’s burdensome carbon emissions regulations and on how we can make America energy independent again. Check out my interview⬇️

Make sure to catch my interview with Greg Drake this morning on @beechtreenews!
streamdb7web.securenetsystem…
Spent some time with my friends in Hancock County yesterday discussing economic growth with Hawesville Mayor Robby McCormick, Hancock County Chamber of Commerce, and the team at Domtar. #KY02

As Health Subcommittee Chair, I’m committed to leading the fight against cancer. Yesterday, I met with representatives from the KY Alliance for Childhood Cancer and the KY Pancreatic Cancer Network to discuss what we’ve been doing in my subcommittee to support their efforts.

While families struggle with rising costs, the Biden Admin’s priorities are not in line with the American people. The Energy Department should be focused on lowering energy prices- instead, they’re focused on banning certain light bulbs and gas stoves. foxnews.com/politics/biden-a…

Under Bidenomics the United States’ Credit Rating has been downgraded again—for only the SECOND time in U.S. history. 
The first? Under the Obama-Biden Administration in 2011. I’m committed to cutting wasteful spending to get our country back on track. foxbusiness.com/politics/bid…

Today we honor the courage and sacrifice of Purple Heart recipients who have been wounded or killed defending our nation.

Your service and sacrifices will always be remembered.

I was proud to sign onto @RepPfluger’s CRA disapproving of President Biden’s Circumvention of Lawful Pathways rule, which contains loopholes that cartels have exploited to traffic deadly drugs into our country. President Biden must be held accountable for his failed policies.
Happy 233rd Birthday to the @uscoastguard. Thank you for standing at the ready to protect our coasts and waterways. Thank you to all Coast Guardsmen for your service to our nation!

Last week I enjoyed meeting with students from @AmericanLegion's Boys Nation and Girls Nation. I’m glad to meet with Kentucky’s next generation of young leaders while they learn the value of being engaged citizens!

Did you miss the latest installment of Brett’s Bulletin? Sign up below to get our next edition right to your inbox!

guthrie.house.gov/forms/form…

I’ve heard from constituents about the challenges they’re facing in obtaining passports. I’m joining with @RepMcGarvey and @RepThomasMassie to call on the State Department to open a Passport Center in Louisville to help with the national backlog. whas11.com/article/news/loca…

As the Representative for Fort Knox, and many veterans, I am committed to delivering for our military and our veterans. This week, I voted to fully fund veteran's healthcare, VA programs, and other veterans benefits all while cutting wasteful spending.
Students with @KentuckyFFA are the future of agriculture in our communities. I enjoyed meeting with them this week to discuss the upcoming Farm Bill.

Last week I was happy to join with my colleagues on the House Floor to vote for the Animal Drug User Fee Agreements to make sure our beloved pets and farm animals are healthy, promoting human health in the process.

If you’re having trouble with receiving the veterans benefits you deserve from a government agency, my team may be able to help. This year we’ve been helping over 100 veterans! Reach out to my Bowling Green office 270-842-9896 if you need assistance!

Congratulations to @RepHalRogers on having the Monticello armory named in his honor. This is a fitting tribute to his dedication to our great commonwealth and the Kentucky @NationalGuard. I am honored to call him my colleague and friend. wymt.com/2023/07/24/national…

Kentucky’s 2nd District has many premier destinations to explore our rich culture and natural beauty- which is why I love to call it home. I recently met with Kentucky tourism officials to discuss how we can work together to boost tourism in #KY02.

I’m proud that my bill to support those struggling with substance use disorder, The SUPPORT for Patients and Communities Reauthorization Act, passed out of the Energy and Commerce Committee unanimously yesterday. guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

Still haven’t received your federal tax refund? In the past 6 months, my casework team has been able to recover over $400,000 that was being held up from the IRS. If you need assistance, please call my Bowling Green office at 270-842-9896.

Today, I was proud to vote for the NDAA. This bill will invest in our men and women in uniform, including the largest servicemember pay raise in over 20 years and additional funding to increase housing allowances. You can read my full statement here: guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…
TUNE IN: As Chairman of the Energy and Commerce Committee’s Health Subcommittee, I’m gaveling in today’s subcommittee markup, which includes several of my own bills: piped.video/watch?v=328z80bG…

REMINDER: The IRS will never contact you via email, text message, or social media to ask for personal information and it’s important to stay vigilant on mailings as well. irs.gov/newsroom/irs-securit…

I just met with the Kentucky Council for Exceptional Children to discuss how we can support special education in KY-02. One step is working to recruit high quality professionals to serve the needs of these children and their families, which I am committed to doing in Congress.

I recently met with Flex Films in Elizabethtown who has won national awards for their outstanding work across numerous continents. We must work to create policy to spur economic growth and keep good manufacturing jobs with international footprints here in Kentucky!
Beth and I are praying for our Bowling Green police officer and his family. Our thoughts and prayers are with the men and women who serve our city.

Last week I spoke with Dr. Juston Pate & his team at ECTC on how they can play a vital role in addressing the workforce challenges associated with growing industry in the area. I will continue to work as co-chair of the Apprenticeship Caucus to promote workforce education.

From Middletown to Morgantown and Bowling Green to Brandenburg, the love you and I have for this country stretches across Kentucky’s 2nd District. Beth and I wish everyone a safe and happy Independence Day!

This week I toured family-owned Spantech Conveyors who recently opened a new 142,000 square foot facility in Glasgow, creating jobs and providing opportunities for dozens of families in their local community. There are big things happening in Kentucky’s 2nd District!

Edwin Smith served in the Air Force during World War II and was missing several medals he earned for his military service. This week, I was proud to present the 100-year old veteran with his replacement medals he has been missing and thank him for his service.

It’s  always an honor to have a student win the Congressional Award Gold Medal from KY-02, this year our district was one of the few across the nation to have TWO recipients receive this high honor. Congratulations to Ashley Nevison and Raven Brackens!
I was proud to welcome hardworking steelworkers from Kentucky to the U.S. Capitol to talk about how we can keep good-paying jobs in the 2nd District and across Kentucky.

As Chair of E&C's Health Subcommittee, I’m working to ensure that people who want to overcome their substance use disorder continue to have access to treatment & recovery services. Today I held a 2nd hearing as part of my efforts to reauthorize key programs that expire this year.

I met with the Kentucky Association of Health Care Facilities and discussed how to recruit more individuals into health care careers. I'm focused on workforce shortages in health care and introduced a bill to bolster the nursing workforce in nursing homes.

I was proud to vote to recognize Juneteenth. I reflect on how far our country has come since President Lincoln, who was from Kentucky, issued the Emancipation Proclamation and commit to further progress towards a more perfect Union.

Today we commemorate the critical point in U.S. history when the horrible sin of slavery was ended. Though President Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation to free enslaved people in Jan. 1863, it wasn't until this day in 1865 that the news of freedom reached Galveston, TX.

Happy Father’s Day! There is no greater or more rewarding job than being a father to my two daughters, Caroline and Elizabeth, and son, Robby, and now a grandfather to Rowan and Laine. Hope everyone has a great day celebrating or remembering their fathers with loved ones.

I recently met with an independent grocer & wholesaler from KY. Independently owned grocery stores are unique & play an integral role in the communities they serve. I'm proud to support #smallbiz & polices that lower inflation and increase energy production to lower food costs.

I enjoyed meeting with @universityofky coaches John Calipari and Rachel Lawson, along with the University of Kentucky’s Athletics Director Mitch Barnhart, to discuss the future of college athletics. #BBN

Today is the U.S. Army’s 248th birthday. Please join me in wishing the Army a happy birthday & thanking soldiers who continue the Army's mission. I was proud to serve in the 101st Airborne Division after graduating from West Point & am honored to represent @FortKnoxKY's soldiers.
As we celebrate Flag Day and proudly fly the U.S. flag, I encourage you to reflect on the sacrifices of service members and their families across the country that keep our flag flying.

The American flag is a symbol of the freedoms that many Americans have fought and died for. For my grandmother, the flag was a symbol of the ultimate sacrifice when it was presented to her after my uncle was killed in the Korean War.
guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

.@MammothCaveNP is a KY treasure. After discussions with the park's leadership & local community leaders, I introduced a bill to expand this park to increase tourism, preserve cultural heritage artifacts & protect wildlife. I'm proud to work with @LeaderMcConnell on this effort.

I always enjoy speaking with my friends at the Home Builders Association of Kentucky. I recently met with them in D.C. and discussed my role on the Energy and Commerce Committee and how we’re taking action to fight rising energy prices and support small businesses in #KY02.

At 4:35 p.m. ET today, I’m joining @terrymeiners on @840WHAS.

Listen LIVE here: whas.iheart.com/featured/ter…

I was proud to join the community in Morgantown at the dedication of Charles Black City Park’s 1813 Freedom Park and discuss local issues. It's great to see Kentuckians in Butler County and across #KY02 show what it means to never forget the sacrifices of our troops and veterans.

On the anniversary of D-Day, we reflect on the bravery of American & Allied troops who stormed Nazi-occupied Normandy 79 years ago. These heroes’ courage during the largest air, land, & sea invasion ultimately helped liberate Europe & protected the freedoms we hold dear today.

Happy Birthday Kentucky!

Today we celebrate Kentucky becoming the 15th state 231 years ago.

Our ambulance personnel in #KY02 are often the very first people at the scene of an emergency, and these heroes’ quick actions save lives. I enjoyed meeting with the Kentucky Ambulance Providers Association on legislative issues that directly impact their line of work.

ICYMI: I voted to crack down on fentanyl by permanently banning variations of fentanyl, also known as fentanyl analogues. 
 
Fentanyl analogues can be even deadlier than fentanyl.
 
This helps stop fentanyl analogues from being created in the first place. 
foxnews.com/politics/most-de…

As you gather with family and friends this Memorial Day, remember we're able to gather together in the greatest country on Earth because of service members who gave the ultimate sacrifice. On Memorial Day, I honor my uncle, SFC Robert Guthrie, who was killed in the Korean War.

I met with a current and a retired educator in Kentucky about policies that prevent some public servants from being able to fully collect retirement benefits they paid into. I’m supporting the Social Security Fairness Act to help them receive their earned benefits.

For Americans ages 18 to 49, analysis shows fentanyl is the top cause of death. Action is needed now to address this crisis.

Today I voted for the HALT Fentanyl Act to ban fentanyl analogues and give law enforcement the tools needed to crack down on illicit fentanyl trafficking.

During National Police Week, I met with family members of the late Deputy Jerry Critchelow. I enjoyed learning more about Deputy Critchelow’s life of service from his family. Last week I voted to honor officers, such as Deputy Critchelow, for their acts of heroism and service.

Yesterday I went to the House floor to press for the passage of the HALT Fentanyl Act. We must get these poisons out of our communities. This bill would permanently ban fentanyl analogues and ensure that many of these poisons do not become street legal.

More than 1 in 3 people in KY are on Medicaid. My bill, the MVP Act, would help give states the flexibility to make high-cost therapies and cures for rare diseases available under Medicaid without raising taxes or cutting other state programs. MVP Act passed @HouseCommerce today.

I enjoyed speaking to Kentuckians for Better Transportation this week in D.C. As a member of @housecommerce, I’m working to lower energy costs to make fuel for all modes of transportation cheaper for travel and the delivery of goods across Kentucky and the country.

Last month the House passed the Protection of Women and Girls in Sports Act. I voted to safeguard women’s sports and ensure a level playing field by preventing biological males from competing in women’s sports at schools that receive federal funding.

This week I had the honor of welcoming Kentuckians who are veterans of WWII and the Korean and Vietnam wars. They traveled to our nation’s capital to see the monuments in honor of their service and sacrifices. I’m proud to support and serve these heroes as their representative.

This week I voted for the Save Our Gas Stoves Act in @housecommerce to protect Americans’ access and choice to use gas stoves. This bill ensures that the Biden Administration can’t finalize its ridiculous proposed regulations that would ban many gas stoves on the market.

I’m proud to #BackTheBlue and vote for pro-law enforcement bills, including memorializing law enforcement officers who lost their lives in the line of duty, condemning the defund the police movement, and making assaulting law enforcement officers a deportable offense. #PoliceWeek
guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

The MVP Act that @repannaeshoo & I are leading passed in @housecommerce Health Subcommittee markup. MVP Act:

✅provides more Americans access to high-cost & potentially life-changing treatments
✅better aligns incentives in health care 
✅ultimately reduces costs of patient care

At 10 a.m. ET today, I’m chairing a @housecommerce Health Subcommittee markup of 17 bills to strengthen Medicare, lower health costs, & unleash price transparency. My bill, MVP Act, is being considered and would increase access to life-changing treatments. piped.video/live/0PECdnB1B10…
guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

I’m proud to reintroduce the TRUSTED Broadband Networks Act, which will be considered in @housecommerce subcommittee markup tomorrow. My bill streamlines the permitting process to help rural providers more quickly remove telecommunications equipment from bad actors.

During #PoliceWeek, I want to thank law enforcement officers who work to combat crime and get illicit fentanyl off the streets to keep our communities safe. I'm proud to support a resolution in Congress that recognizes law enforcement’s acts of sacrifice and heroism. #BackTheBlue

Happy Mother’s Day! I’m incredibly thankful for my wife and mother of our three children, Beth, and I’m also excited to celebrate Mother’s Day with my daughter Caroline, who is now a mother of two with our newest grandchild who was born in April.

I voted for the Protecting Taxpayers and Victims of Unemployment Fraud Act to incentivize states to go after criminals who committed fraud to steal unemployment insurance payments. Criminals stole Americans’ identities to get these payments, and those funds should be recovered.

Today I was proud to do my part in keeping Republicans’ Commitment to America by voting to restore law and order at the Southern border with H.R. 2. Meanwhile, President Biden is ending Title 42 protections today, which is resulting in a surge of migrants at the Southern border.

In KY, fentanyl was involved in 73% of overdose deaths in 2021. On #NationalFentanylAwarenessDay, I want to raise awareness of the dangers of fentanyl and reaffirm my commitment to pass the HALT Fentanyl Act. If you need help, SAMHSA’s National Helpline is 1-800-662-HELP (4357).

During #MilitaryAppreciationMonth, I want to recognize our heroes and their families at @FortKnoxKY. Our service members sacrifice so much to keep us safe. I would like to express my support, respect, and appreciation for our military in #KY02 and beyond.

I met with employees, including veterans, with InspiriTec who help support Fort Knox’s and other military installations’ missions. #KY02 has a great community of civilians who work with service members. We discussed federal programs to support veterans in the workforce.

I joined community members in Grayson County in observing the National Day of Prayer. Our Founding Fathers found this right so important to our democracy that they put this freedom in the First Amendment. I was proud to exercise the right to pray with community members.

I enjoyed meeting with firefighters and EMTs who help keep Leitchfield safe, and local celebrity, Willena Skees, who is known as the “Firehouse Mom” and known all over Grayson County for her love for the community and cooking. At the meeting, I provided an update on legislation.

It was an honor to present Natalie Williams with a replacement gold medal from the 2007 Special Olympics. The original medal was lost when a tornado hit the Special Olympics athlete's family home. I'm happy Natalie again has this symbol of her achievement on the world stage.

Kentucky’s Second District is home to passionate and caring educators. On #TeacherAppreciationDay, I want to thank these teachers for their work to teach and encourage students to be their best and achieve their dreams.

I was happy to recognize Gavin Wilson yesterday at South Warren High School for earning an appointment to the U.S. Air Force Academy. I was proud to nominate him. Please join me in congratulating Gavin on this appointment!

During #NationalParkWeek, I want to recognize @MammothCaveNP and @LincolnBirthNPS in my district and thank National Park Service employees and volunteers for their work to preserve these beautiful parks. I encourage people to visit these incredible National Parks in #KY02.

Please join me in congratulating Bethlehem High School student Parker Greer for receiving an appointment to the U.S. Naval Academy. I was proud to nominate Parker, and this week I recognized him for this achievement at an event with his family, friends, and educators.

Congrats Nelson County HS student Dakota Kirchner for winning the Congressional Art Competition in #KY02! Thanks to all the talented students who participated and dedicated educators and volunteer judges for helping make this year’s competition a success. guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

I enjoyed being a guest speaker at Munfordville Elementary. I shared my duties as a representative and gave a presentation on the three branches of government. Educators had given these students a solid foundation on civics, and the students asked great questions!

Tune in: At 10 a.m. ET today @housecommerce’s Health Subcommittee is examining policies to lower health care costs and empower patients through increased transparency and competition in the health care system. My bill, the MVP Act, is part of this hearing: republicans-energycommerce.h…

While our men and women in uniform serve, over 1.6 million of their children face unique challenges at home and abroad. With April being the Month of the Military Child, I join our service members to celebrate and support the children of our bravest across the 2nd District.

I was proud to meet with the Congressional App Challenge winners from Kentucky’s 2nd District - Megan Shirley and Clay Madison – at the #HouseofCode Capitol Hill reception in the U.S. Capitol with other winners across the nation. Please join me in congratulating Megan and Clay!
guthrie.house.gov/news/docum…

I'm proud to introduce the MVP Act with @RepAnnaEshoo, @RepJohnJoyce, @RepAuchincloss, and @RepMMM. This bill would increase access to life-altering medications and ensure states are not on the hook for reimbursing drug manufacturers for treatments that do not work for patients.

I voted for the Parents Bill of Rights Act to ensure parents have a seat at the table on their child's education. This passed the House & upholds key rights for parents, including the right to know what's being taught, protect their child's privacy, & know about violent activity.

On Tax Day, you can thank President Biden and congressional Democrats for raising taxes on Americans, including people who make under $400,000, and authorizing funds to beef up IRS enforcement and hire thousands of new IRS agents. House Republicans voted to repeal this funding.

On the House floor, we remembered our neighbors who we lost in Louisville. I prayed with members of KY delegation & my other colleagues for the families of those who lost their lives & the officer still in the hospital. I'm grateful for officers' swift response that saved lives.

Americans need affordable, reliable energy. I toured Paradise Combined Cycle Plant in Muhlenberg County & discussed TVA's policies to meet the growing demand for energy. I voted for H.R. 1 to increase U.S. energy production & reform permitting to help deliver this needed energy.

I enjoyed meeting with members of the Barren County community at a Kiwanis Club of Glasgow meeting. I shared that I’m focused on advancing U.S. energy independence. If we make our country dependent on dictators for our energy needs, then we make ourselves vulnerable to dictators.

I was proud to join a community celebration in Glasgow for WWII veteran Edwin Smith’s 100th birthday. I presented a Congressional Record in honor of this Kentucky veteran’s service to our country and momentous birthday.
